## Step 4: Plan Fix

**Assess complexity. Determine fix scope.**

### 4.1 Complexity Assessment

Evaluate the bug:

| Criteria | Simple Bug | Complex Bug |
|----------|------------|-------------|
| Fix type | Typo, off-by-one, wrong operator | Logic error, data flow issue |
| Entry points | Single entry point to buggy code | Multiple entry points possible |
| Severity | Nit-level (cosmetic, minor UX) | Blocking (crash, data loss, security) |
| Root cause | Clear, isolated | Subtle, easy to reintroduce |

### 4.2 Defence-in-Depth Decision

```
IF simple bug (all criteria match "Simple Bug"):
  → Single-point fix at root cause is sufficient

IF complex bug (any criteria match "Complex Bug"):
  → Defence-in-depth required:
    - Fix at root cause
    - Add validation at intermediate layers
    - Each layer that handles the bad value should validate
```

### 4.3 Document Fix Plan

**Output to human:**

```
Fix Plan:

Root cause: [file:line] — [description]

Complexity: [Simple / Complex]

Proposed fix:
- Root: [what to change at root cause]

IF complex bug:
- Layer 1: [validation to add]
- Layer 2: [validation to add]

Files affected:
- [file1]
- [file2]

Ready to execute fix?
```

{{ present_for_validation(
    pre_validation="Present fix plan to human for review.",
    post_validation="APPEND fix plan to the design document"
) }}

